<subSubSection id="979FE785FFB0E47C5A86FEE0FCCEED2E" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="1317" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF3AB40EFFB0E4635A86FEE0FE6DEF85" blockId="15.[177,1085,379,457]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Body length 
<quantity id="187D19EBFFB0E463582EFEE7FD14EFDD" box="[537,657,379,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316" unit="mm" value="3.15" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.9">2.9-3.4 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="47BEA88BFFB0E463591FFEE7FCF6EFDD" box="[808,883,379,401]" captionStart="Figs 40-48" captionStartId="14.[177,217,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[188,1079,495,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[178,1085,495,1439]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 40-48: Oxypoda flavissima nov.sp.: (40) habitus; (41) forebody; (42) antenna; (43) head in lateral view; (44) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (45) paramere; (46) female tergite VIII; (47) female sternite VIII; (48) spermatheca. Scale bars: 40: 1.0 mm; 41: 0.5 mm; 42-43, 46-47: 0.2 mm; 44-45, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5430673/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
. Coloration distinctive: whole body, except eyes, uniformly yellowish; middle of abdominal tergite VI occasionally weakly infuscate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF3AB40EFFB0E4635A86FE4BFD04ECD9" blockId="15.[177,1085,471,661]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">
Head (
<figureCitation id="47BEA88BFFB0E4635AC2FE4BFEEFEFA1" box="[245,362,471,493]" captionStart="Figs 40-48" captionStartId="14.[177,217,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[188,1079,495,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[178,1085,495,1439]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 40-48: Oxypoda flavissima nov.sp.: (40) habitus; (41) forebody; (42) antenna; (43) head in lateral view; (44) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (45) paramere; (46) female tergite VIII; (47) female sternite VIII; (48) spermatheca. Scale bars: 40: 1.0 mm; 41: 0.5 mm; 42-43, 46-47: 0.2 mm; 44-45, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5430673/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">Figs 41, 43</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.1 times as wide as long; punctation rather dense and very fine, barely distinguishable from the pronounced microreticulation; pubescence short, whitish, and decumbent; eyes moderately small, approximately 0.6-0.7 times as long as postocular region in dorsal view. Maxillary palpi with penultimate palpomere 3- 3.5 times as long as broad. Antennae gradually incrassate apically; antennomere IV weakly transverse; X approximately 1.5 times as wide as long; XI approximately as long as the combined length of IX and X (
<figureCitation id="47BEA88BFFB0E463581EFDE3FDF3ECD9" box="[553,630,639,661]" captionStart="Figs 40-48" captionStartId="14.[177,217,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[188,1079,495,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[178,1085,495,1439]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 40-48: Oxypoda flavissima nov.sp.: (40) habitus; (41) forebody; (42) antenna; (43) head in lateral view; (44) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (45) paramere; (46) female tergite VIII; (47) female sternite VIII; (48) spermatheca. Scale bars: 40: 1.0 mm; 41: 0.5 mm; 42-43, 46-47: 0.2 mm; 44-45, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5430673/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF3AB40EFFB0E4635A86FD38FD61ED65" blockId="15.[177,1085,675,809]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="47BEA88BFFB0E4635B13FD3FFEEAECF5" box="[292,367,675,697]" captionStart="Figs 40-48" captionStartId="14.[177,217,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[188,1079,495,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[178,1085,495,1439]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 40-48: Oxypoda flavissima nov.sp.: (40) habitus; (41) forebody; (42) antenna; (43) head in lateral view; (44) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (45) paramere; (46) female tergite VIII; (47) female sternite VIII; (48) spermatheca. Scale bars: 40: 1.0 mm; 41: 0.5 mm; 42-43, 46-47: 0.2 mm; 44-45, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5430673/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.25 times as wide as long and 1.35 times as wide as head, widest slightly behind middle; posterior angles weakly marked; punctation dense, shallow, fine, and partly somewhat ill-defined, but slightly more distinct than that of head; interstices on average narrower than diameter of punctures and with distinct microreticulation; pubescence whitish, short, and decumbent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF3AB40EFFB0E4635A86FCABFD8AED95" blockId="15.[177,1085,823,985]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">
Elytra approximately 0.9 times as long and 1.15 times as wide as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="47BEA88BFFB0E46359D6FCABFBB5ED01" box="[993,1072,823,845]" captionStart="Figs 40-48" captionStartId="14.[177,217,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[188,1079,495,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[178,1085,495,1439]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 40-48: Oxypoda flavissima nov.sp.: (40) habitus; (41) forebody; (42) antenna; (43) head in lateral view; (44) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (45) paramere; (46) female tergite VIII; (47) female sternite VIII; (48) spermatheca. Scale bars: 40: 1.0 mm; 41: 0.5 mm; 42-43, 46-47: 0.2 mm; 44-45, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5430673/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1316">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
); punctation dense, weakly granulose, and somewhat more distinct than that of pronotum; interstices on average narrower than diameter of punctures and with shallow microsculpture; pubescence similar to that of pronotum. Hind wings apparently fully developed. Metatarsomere I somewhat longer than the combined length of II-III, but shorter than the combined length of II-IV.
</paragraph>
